notes: Area west of Nefta: chott used for the Lars homestead[1]
Scenes shot in the town include the exterior of the Mos Eisley Cantina. An old mosque outside the town was used for exterior shots of Obi-Wan Kenobi's house[1]
Location for the deleted exterior scenes with Luke and Biggs Darklighter; also used as a backdrop in the Special Edition for the scene showing Luke's landspeeder heading towards Mos Eisley[1][18]
Exterior scenes during the battle of Hoth[20]

Location used for the Great Pit of Carkoon scene [21][22]  Additional footage for the special edition of A New Hope of stormtroopers finding evidence of droids was shot here and cut in with original shots from La Grande Dune, Tunisia [23][24]
Footage of limestone karst mountains which was later composited into the film for the backdrop of Kashyyyk[9]

Several Tatooine scenes:[15][17]  Mesquite Flat Sand Dunes - scene where R2D2 goes his separate way after he and C3P0 crash their escape pod on Tatooine (spliced with footage shot in Tunisia) Artists Palette & Golden Canyon - Canyon where R2D2 is abducted by Jawas (spliced with footage shot at Sidi Bouhlel, Tunisia) Artist's Drive - Where the miniature Sandcrawler was filmed for the shot of R2D2 being carried up to it by Jawas Desolation Canyon - Canyon where Tusken Raiders mount Bantha before Luke Skywalker is attacked (spliced with Sidi Bouhlel footage) Dante's View - panoramic establishing shot of Mos Eisley (spliced with Sidi Bouhlel footage of Luke and Obi-Wan standing on rocky outcrop)
Footage of mountain scenery which was later composited into the film for the backdrop of the planet Alderaan[12]
Sand dunes west of Nefta used to film the landing area of the escape pod of C-3PO and R2-D2[1][13][14]
Used for courtyard shots and Lars dinner scene. The homestead also featured in Attack of the Clones[1][7]

The volcano erupted during filming of Episode III and Lucasfilm sent camera crews to shoot several angles of the eruption; footage was later composited into the background of the scenes set on Mustafar including the lightsaber duel of Obi-Wan Kenobi and Anakin Skywalker.[10][11]
Location of the lightsaber duel between Qui-Gonn Jinn & Darth Maul; Mos Espa[1]
Aerial footage of limestone karst mountains which was later composited into the film for the approach over the Battle of Kashyyyk [8]

Several Tatooine scenes:[13][19]  Canyon where R2D2 is abducted by Jawas (spliced with footage shot at Death Valley, USA) Canyon where Tusken Raiders attack Luke Skywalker (spliced with Death Valley footage) Scene of wrecked Sandcrawler after attack by Imperial stormtroopers Also features in The Phantom Menace.[1]
location: Shubiel Gorge, Sidi Bouhlel (or Sidi Bou Helal), near Tozeur

notes: Two Tatooine scenes:  C-3P0 and R2D2 walk up to the Palace of Jabba the Hutt on Tatooine. "Lost scene" of Luke Skywalker working on a new lightsaber in a cave overlooking the Millennium Falcon and his X-wing, followed by R2D2 and C3PO starting their trek to Jabba's palace.
location: Twenty-Mule Team Canyon, Death Valley, California

notes: Used for Anakin and Padmé's wedding scene overlooking Lake Como [6]
